The paper deals with 3D Morphable Models, which are commonly used in computer vision and graphics. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves statistical methods and machine learning techniques, which suggest cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with 3D surfaces and shape modelling, which could fall under cs.GR (Computer Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves facial detail and expression handling, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
